Bomb kills explosives disposal policemen in South
Two explosive ordnance disposal (EOD) police officers were killed in an explosion while trying to dismantle a bomb on Monday morning in Bacho district of Narathiwat province, according to a report from Hat Yai News Centre.
The report said the incident occurred about 9.50am at Ban Sompoy in tambon Kayomati of Bacho district.
Killed in the explosion were Pol Sub Lt Chaen Warongpaisith, deputy chief of the EOD team of Narathiwat, and Pol Sub Lt Jaroon Mekruang.
There were no other details.